        -:   31:/** \ingroup QR_Module
        -:   32:  *
        -:   33:  * \class ColPivHouseholderQR
        -:   34:  *
        -:   35:  * \brief Householder rank-revealing QR decomposition of a matrix with column-pivoting
        -:   36:  *
        -:   37:  * \tparam MatrixType_ the type of the matrix of which we are computing the QR decomposition
        -:   38:  *
        -:   39:  * This class performs a rank-revealing QR decomposition of a matrix \b A into matrices \b P, \b Q and \b R
        -:   40:  * such that
        -:   41:  * \f[
        -:   42:  *  \mathbf{A} \, \mathbf{P} = \mathbf{Q} \, \mathbf{R}
        -:   43:  * \f]
        -:   44:  * by using Householder transformations. Here, \b P is a permutation matrix, \b Q a unitary matrix and \b R an
        -:   45:  * upper triangular matrix.
        -:   46:  *
        -:   47:  * This decomposition performs column pivoting in order to be rank-revealing and improve
        -:   48:  * numerical stability. It is slower than HouseholderQR, and faster than FullPivHouseholderQR.
        -:   49:  *
        -:   50:  * This class supports the \link InplaceDecomposition inplace decomposition \endlink mechanism.
        -:   51:  * 
        -:   52:  * \sa MatrixBase::colPivHouseholderQr()
        -:   53:  */
